#📊 Databricks Advanced AI Challenge – End-to-End ML Lakehouse Pipeline


##🚀 Project Overview

This repository documents my 14-day journey through the Databricks Advanced AI Challenge, where I built a complete Machine Learning Lakehouse pipeline using PySpark, Delta Lake, and MLflow.
The goal of this project was to design an end-to-end data and machine learning system that starts from raw event data and produces both predictive insights and personalized recommendations.
Over the course of the challenge, the project evolved from simple data transformations into a complete ML system covering:
Data ingestion
Feature engineering
Machine learning model training
Experiment tracking
Batch inference pipelines
Recommendation systems
Query performance optimization
Delta Lake versioning
System architecture design

##🏗 System Architecture

The project follows a **Lakehouse Architecture**, combining scalable data engineering with machine learning workflows.

Raw Event Data (CSV)
        │
        ▼
Bronze Layer (Delta Tables)
events_delta
        │
        ▼
Silver Layer (Feature Engineering)
user_features
        │
        ▼
Machine Learning Pipeline
Feature Vectorization
        │
        ▼
Model Training
(Logistic Regression & Random Forest)
        │
        ▼
Gold Layer
Predictions Table
final_model_predictions
Parallel Pipeline – Recommendation System
User Interaction Data
        │
        ▼
ALS Collaborative Filtering Model
        │
        ▼
Top-N Product Recommendations
        │
        ▼
Gold Recommendation Table
gold_user_recommendations

##⚙️ Technologies Used

This project leverages modern data engineering and machine learning tools:
Databricks
Apache Spark
PySpark
Delta Lake
MLflow
Spark MLlib
Structured Streaming

##🔄 End-to-End Pipeline Workflow

The full system follows this workflow:
1️⃣ Data Ingestion
Raw event data is ingested and stored in Delta tables in the Bronze layer.

2️⃣ Feature Engineering
User-level behavioral features are generated from event data.
Examples:
Total events
Purchase count
Total spend
Average product price
These are stored in the Silver layer.

3️⃣ Model Training
Machine learning models are trained using Spark MLlib.
Models used:
Logistic Regression (baseline model)
Random Forest (final model)
Evaluation metric:
AUC (Area Under ROC Curve)

4️⃣ Experiment Tracking
All model experiments are tracked using MLflow, logging:
Model parameters
Evaluation metrics
Model artifacts

5️⃣ Batch Inference
The trained model generates predictions for all users and saves results in the Gold layer.

6️⃣ Recommendation System
An ALS Collaborative Filtering model generates Top-5 product recommendations for each user.

7️⃣ Optimization & Governance
Additional engineering work included:
Delta Lake OPTIMIZE
Query explain plan analysis
Runtime optimization
Delta Time Travel
Data versioning


